Class PopupViewWithUiHandlers<C extends UiHandlers>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.ViewImpl
      • com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.PopupViewImpl
        • com.gwtplatform.mvp.client.PopupViewWithUiHandlers<C>
  • Type Parameters:
    C - Your UiHandlers interface type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IsWidget, HasUiHandlers<C>, PopupView, View
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EditManufacturerView, EditRatingView

    public abstract class PopupViewWithUiHandlers<C extends UiHandlers>
extends PopupViewImpl
implements HasUiHandlers<C>
    Base class for a PopupView that implements the HasUiHandlers interface. You should always call setUiHandlers(UiHandlers) from your presenter 's constructor.

    Important! Never call getUiHandlers() inside your constructor since the UiHandlers are not yet set.

    Author:
    Christian Goudreau, Philippe Beaudoin
